  "prompt": "Can we change marks of autonomous marksheet?",
  "response": "Modifying marks on an official autonomous marksheet is generally considered unethical and is not legally permissible. Marksheets are official documents issued by educational institutions to certify students' academic performance. Changing the marks on such documents would be considered forgery and could lead to serious consequences, including legal action, academic penalties, and reputational damage.\n\nIf there is a genuine error or valid reason for a mark change, you should contact the relevant academic office or authorities at the institution where the marksheet was issued. Most institutions have procedures in place to address errors in marksheets through formal channels.",
